<h1>Beaming Audio Documentation</h1>  </div>
</div>
<div class="contents">
<div class="textblock"><p>On the BEAMING SVN, the folder [trunk/Audio/AudioClientServer] folder contains what may be described as a "stable snapshot" of the audio software for BEAMING. This documentation is generated from the classes therein. Apart from this html-version, also a Qt Help file is generated, which can be included in QtCreator to work the same way as other Qt Documentation as described on <a href="http://doc.qt.nokia.com/qtcreator/creator-help.html#adding-external-documentation.">http://doc.qt.nokia.com/qtcreator/creator-help.html#adding-external-documentation.</a></p>
<p>The subfolders contain the main classes as well as separate QtCreator projects and matching source code:</p>
<p>Folder overview:</p>
<ul>
<li>[Classes] contains Qt classes providing basic functionality that are used in all the different programs<ul>
<li>This documentation is so far mainly concerned with these classes</li>
<li>The use of these classes should be the main focus for anyone integrating use of the audio streaming. This could for instance be for purposes like determining how to move a mouth or for implementing a proxy.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>[AudioClientCli] implements a command line audio client using the client types to connect to an audio server and stream audio<ul>
<li>mainly tested in linux.</li>
<li>Pierre from UB has succesfully used this in windows, compiled with msvc</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>[AudioServerCli] implements a command line audio server<ul>
<li>mainly tested in linux.</li>
<li>Pierre from UB has succesfully used this in windows, compiled with msvc</li>
<li>If a Scene server is available, public address and port of the server will be shared on this</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>[SimpleAudioListener] is a very simple implementation of how one may access a specific audio stream from an AudioServer using the <a class="el" href="class_rak_cli.html" title="class containing the overall interface for connecting and identifying to an Audio Server...">RakCli</a> class<ul>
<li>currently only tested in linux</li>
<li>As long as you include the proper headers etc., this should also be possible to use and compile in windows, including in visual studio</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p>Additional folders with examples will be provided once they are ready.</p>
<p>Anyone willing to create Visual Studio solutions that create DLL's to import the classes in XVR are welcome to help with this.</p>
<p>Quick overview of how to integrate the audio streaming:</p>
<ul>
<li>Compile the dependencies on the BEAMING SVN accourding to their respective guides<ul>
<li>RakNet - required for streaming</li>
<li>Beaming Scene - required to locate the audio server address and port<ul>
<li>Audio server is puplished as an AUDIO client according to the BEAMING Scene Service documentation</li>
<li>When accessing the Scene Service, make sure to set the "viewer" parameter of startclient() to 1</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>(Portaudio) - only required if recording or playing audio</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Take inspiration from the implementations of SimpleAudioListener and AudioClientCli</li>
<li>In particular the following classes are relevant for minimum implementation<ul>
<li><a class="el" href="class_rak_cli.html" title="class containing the overall interface for connecting and identifying to an Audio Server...">RakCli</a></li>
<li><a class="el" href="class_audio_interface.html" title="Interface for asynchronous communication between audio modules.">AudioInterface</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>A definition of relevant client types (<a class="el" href="rakinfo_8h.html#a3c17bff6fe46b8320aaff27c1fbac19c" title="tClientType is an enum for defining our internal (audio) client types">tClientType</a>) that can be used to identify to the audio server can be found in <a class="el" href="rakinfo_8h.html" title="contains general extended RakNet information used by both RakCli and RakServ">rakinfo.h</a></li>
</ul>
<p>For questions, please contact the AAU BEAMING Group on <a href="mailto:beaming-aalborg@es.aau.dk">beaming-aalborg@es.aau.dk</a> </p>
